65// Editing style properties must be preserved during editing operation.
66// e.g. when a user inserts a new paragraph, all properties listed here must be copied to the new paragraph.
67static const CSSPropertyID editingProperties[] = {
68 CSSPropertyCaretColor,
69 CSSPropertyColor,
70 CSSPropertyFontFamily,
71 CSSPropertyFontSize,
72 CSSPropertyFontStyle,
73 CSSPropertyFontVariantCaps,
74 CSSPropertyFontWeight,
75 CSSPropertyLetterSpacing,
76 CSSPropertyOrphans,
77 CSSPropertyTextAlign,
78 CSSPropertyTextIndent,
79 CSSPropertyTextTransform,
80 CSSPropertyWhiteSpace,
81 CSSPropertyWidows,
82 CSSPropertyWordSpacing,
83#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
84 CSSPropertyWebkitTapHighlightColor,
85#endif
86 CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect,
87 CSSPropertyWebkitTextFillColor,
88#if ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
89 CSSPropertyWebkitTextSizeAdjust,
90#endif
91 CSSPropertyWebkitTextStrokeColor,
92 CSSPropertyWebkitTextStrokeWidth,
93
94 // Non-inheritable properties
95 CSSPropertyBackgroundColor,
96 CSSPropertyTextDecoration,
97};
98
99const unsigned numAllEditingProperties = WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(editingProperties);
100const unsigned numInheritableEditingProperties = numAllEditingProperties - 2;
101
102enum EditingPropertiesToInclude { OnlyInheritableEditingProperties, AllEditingProperties };
103template <class StyleDeclarationType>
104static Ref<MutableStyleProperties> copyEditingProperties(StyleDeclarationType* style, EditingPropertiesToInclude type)
105{
106 if (type == AllEditingProperties)
107 return style->copyPropertiesInSet(editingProperties, numAllEditingProperties);
108 return style->copyPropertiesInSet(editingProperties, numInheritableEditingProperties);
109}
110
111static inline bool isEditingProperty(int id)
112{
113 for (auto& editingProperty : editingProperties) {
114 if (editingProperty == id)
115 return true;
116 }
117 return false;
118}
119
120static Ref<MutableStyleProperties> copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(ComputedStyleExtractor& computedStyle, EditingStyle::PropertiesToInclude propertiesToInclude)
121{
122 switch (propertiesToInclude) {
123 case EditingStyle::OnlyEditingInheritableProperties:
124 return copyEditingProperties(&computedStyle, OnlyInheritableEditingProperties);
125 case EditingStyle::EditingPropertiesInEffect:
126 return copyEditingProperties(&computedStyle, AllEditingProperties);
127 case EditingStyle::AllProperties:
128 break;
129 }
130 return computedStyle.copyProperties();
131}
132
133static Ref<MutableStyleProperties> copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(Node* node, EditingStyle::PropertiesToInclude propertiesToInclude)
134{
135 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyle(node);
136 return copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(computedStyle, propertiesToInclude);
137}

139static RefPtr<CSSValue> extractPropertyValue(const StyleProperties& style, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
140{
141 return style.getPropertyCSSValue(propertyID);
142}
143
144static RefPtr<CSSValue> extractPropertyValue(ComputedStyleExtractor& computedStyle, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
145{
146 return computedStyle.propertyValue(propertyID);
147}
148
149template<typename T>
150int identifierForStyleProperty(T& style, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
151{
152 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = extractPropertyValue(style, propertyID);
153 if (propertyID == CSSPropertyFontStyle && is<CSSFontStyleValue>(value) && downcast<CSSFontStyleValue>(value.get())->isItalicOrOblique())
154 return CSSValueItalic;
155 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value))
156 return 0;
157 return downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value).valueID();
158}

166class HTMLElementEquivalent {
167 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
168public:
169 HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyID, CSSValueID primitiveValue, const QualifiedName& tagName);
170 virtual ~HTMLElementEquivalent() = default;
171
172 virtual bool matches(const Element& element) const { return !m_tagName || element.hasTagName(*m_tagName); }
173 virtual bool hasAttribute() const { return false; }
174 virtual bool propertyExistsInStyle(const EditingStyle& style) const { return style.m_mutableStyle && style.m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(m_propertyID); }
175 virtual bool valueIsPresentInStyle(Element&, const EditingStyle&) const;
176 virtual void addToStyle(Element*, EditingStyle*) const;
177
178protected:
179 HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyID);
180 HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyID, const QualifiedName& tagName);
181 const CSSPropertyID m_propertyID;
182 const RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> m_primitiveValue;
183 const QualifiedName* m_tagName { nullptr }; // We can store a pointer because HTML tag names are const global.
184};
185
186HTMLElementEquivalent::HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyID id)
187 : m_propertyID(id)
188{
189}
190
191HTMLElementEquivalent::HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyID id, const QualifiedName& tagName)
192 : m_propertyID(id)
193 , m_tagName(&tagName)
194{
195}
196
197HTMLElementEquivalent::HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyID id, CSSValueID primitiveValue, const QualifiedName& tagName)
198 : m_propertyID(id)
199 , m_primitiveValue(CSSPrimitiveValue::createIdentifier(primitiveValue))
200 , m_tagName(&tagName)
201{
202 ASSERT(primitiveValue != CSSValueInvalid);
203}
204
205bool HTMLElementEquivalent::valueIsPresentInStyle(Element& element, const EditingStyle& style) const
206{
207 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = style.m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(m_propertyID);
208 return matches(element) && is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value) && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value).valueID() == m_primitiveValue->valueID();
209}
210
211void HTMLElementEquivalent::addToStyle(Element*, EditingStyle* style) const
212{
213 style->setProperty(m_propertyID, m_primitiveValue->cssText());
214}

216class HTMLTextDecorationEquivalent : public HTMLElementEquivalent {
217public:
218 HTMLTextDecorationEquivalent(CSSValueID primitiveValue, const QualifiedName& tagName)
219 : HTMLElementEquivalent(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, primitiveValue, tagName)
220 , m_isUnderline(primitiveValue == CSSValueUnderline)
221 {
222 }
223
224 bool propertyExistsInStyle(const EditingStyle& style) const override
225 {
226 if (changeInStyle(style) != TextDecorationChange::None)
227 return true;
228
229 if (!style.m_mutableStyle)
230 return false;
231
232 auto& mutableStyle = *style.m_mutableStyle;
233 return mutableStyle.getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect)
234 || mutableStyle.getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
235 }
236
237 bool valueIsPresentInStyle(Element& element, const EditingStyle& style) const override
238 {
239 if (!matches(element))
240 return false;
241 auto change = changeInStyle(style);
242 if (change != TextDecorationChange::None)
243 return change == TextDecorationChange::Add;
244 RefPtr<CSSValue> styleValue = style.m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
245 if (!styleValue)
246 styleValue = style.m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
247 return is<CSSValueList>(styleValue) && downcast<CSSValueList>(*styleValue).hasValue(m_primitiveValue.get());
248 }
249
250private:
251 TextDecorationChange changeInStyle(const EditingStyle& style) const
252 {
253 return m_isUnderline ? style.underlineChange() : style.strikeThroughChange();
254 }
255
256 bool m_isUnderline;
257};

259class HTMLAttributeEquivalent : public HTMLElementEquivalent {
260public:
261 HTMLAttributeEquivalent(CSSPropertyID, const QualifiedName& tagName, const QualifiedName& attrName);
262 HTMLAttributeEquivalent(CSSPropertyID, const QualifiedName& attrName);
263
264 bool matches(const Element& element) const override { return HTMLElementEquivalent::matches(element) && element.hasAttribute(m_attrName); }
265 bool hasAttribute() const override { return true; }
266 bool valueIsPresentInStyle(Element&, const EditingStyle&) const override;
267 void addToStyle(Element*, EditingStyle*) const override;
268 virtual RefPtr<CSSValue> attributeValueAsCSSValue(Element*) const;
269 inline const QualifiedName& attributeName() const { return m_attrName; }
270
271protected:
272 const QualifiedName& m_attrName; // We can store a reference because HTML attribute names are const global.
273};

287bool HTMLAttributeEquivalent::valueIsPresentInStyle(Element& element, const EditingStyle& style) const
288{
289 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = attributeValueAsCSSValue(&element);
290 RefPtr<CSSValue> styleValue = style.m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(m_propertyID);
291
292 return compareCSSValuePtr(value, styleValue);
293}
294
295void HTMLAttributeEquivalent::addToStyle(Element* element, EditingStyle* style) const
296{
297 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> value = attributeValueAsCSSValue(element))
298 style->setProperty(m_propertyID, value->cssText());
299}
300
301RefPtr<CSSValue> HTMLAttributeEquivalent::attributeValueAsCSSValue(Element* element) const
302{
303 ASSERT(element);
304 const AtomString& value = element->getAttribute(m_attrName);
305 if (value.isNull())
306 return nullptr;
307
308 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> dummyStyle;
309 dummyStyle = MutableStyleProperties::create();
310 dummyStyle->setProperty(m_propertyID, value);
311 return dummyStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(m_propertyID);
312}

322 : HTMLAttributeEquivalent(CSSPropertyFontSize, HTMLNames::fontTag, HTMLNames::sizeAttr)
323{
324}
325
326RefPtr<CSSValue> HTMLFontSizeEquivalent::attributeValueAsCSSValue(Element* element) const
327{
328 ASSERT(element);
329 const AtomString& value = element->getAttribute(m_attrName);
330 if (value.isNull())
331 return nullptr;
332 CSSValueID size;
333 if (!HTMLFontElement::cssValueFromFontSizeNumber(value, size))
334 return nullptr;
335 return CSSPrimitiveValue::createIdentifier(size);
336}

392static Color cssValueToColor(CSSValue* colorValue)
393{
394 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(colorValue))
395 return Color::transparentBlack;
396
397 CSSPrimitiveValue& primitiveColor = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*colorValue);
398 if (primitiveColor.isRGBColor())
399 return primitiveColor.color();
400
401 return CSSParser::parseColor(colorValue->cssText());
402}
403
404template<typename T>
405static inline Color textColorFromStyle(T& style)
406{
407 return cssValueToColor(extractPropertyValue(style, CSSPropertyColor).get());
408}
409
410template<typename T>
411static inline Color caretColorFromStyle(T& style)
412{
413 return cssValueToColor(extractPropertyValue(style, CSSPropertyCaretColor).get());
414}
415
416template<typename T>
417static inline Color backgroundColorFromStyle(T& style)
418{
419 return cssValueToColor(extractPropertyValue(style, CSSPropertyBackgroundColor).get());
420}

422static inline Color rgbaBackgroundColorInEffect(Node* node)
423{
424 return cssValueToColor(backgroundColorInEffect(node).get());

427static int textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(int textAlign, int direction)
428{
429 switch (textAlign) {
430 case CSSValueCenter:
431 case CSSValueWebkitCenter:
432 return CSSValueCenter;
433 case CSSValueJustify:
434 return CSSValueJustify;
435 case CSSValueLeft:
436 case CSSValueWebkitLeft:
437 return CSSValueLeft;
438 case CSSValueRight:
439 case CSSValueWebkitRight:
440 return CSSValueRight;
441 case CSSValueStart:
442 return direction != CSSValueRtl ? CSSValueLeft : CSSValueRight;
443 case CSSValueEnd:
444 return direction == CSSValueRtl ? CSSValueRight : CSSValueLeft;
445 }
446 return CSSValueInvalid;
447}
448
449template<typename T>
450static int textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(T& style)
451{
452 return textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(identifierForStyleProperty(style, CSSPropertyTextAlign), identifierForStyleProperty(style, CSSPropertyDirection));
453}
454
455void EditingStyle::init(Node* node, PropertiesToInclude propertiesToInclude)
456{
457 if (isTabSpanTextNode(node))
458 node = tabSpanNode(node)->parentNode();
459 else if (isTabSpanNode(node))
460 node = node->parentNode();
461
462 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyleAtPosition(node);
463 // FIXME: It's strange to not set background-color and text-decoration when propertiesToInclude is EditingPropertiesInEffect.
464 // However editing/selection/contains-boundaries.html fails without this ternary.
465 m_mutableStyle = copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(computedStyleAtPosition,
466 propertiesToInclude == EditingPropertiesInEffect ? OnlyEditingInheritableProperties : propertiesToInclude);
467
468 if (propertiesToInclude == EditingPropertiesInEffect) {
469 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> value = backgroundColorInEffect(node))
470 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor, value->cssText());
471 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> value = computedStyleAtPosition.propertyValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect)) {
472 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, value->cssText());
473 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
474 }
475 }
476
477 if (node && node->computedStyle()) {
478 auto* renderStyle = node->computedStyle();
479 removeTextFillAndStrokeColorsIfNeeded(renderStyle);
480 if (renderStyle->fontDescription().keywordSize())
481 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyFontSize, computedStyleAtPosition.getFontSizeCSSValuePreferringKeyword()->cssText());
482 }
483
484 m_shouldUseFixedDefaultFontSize = computedStyleAtPosition.useFixedFontDefaultSize();
485 extractFontSizeDelta();
486}
487
488void EditingStyle::removeTextFillAndStrokeColorsIfNeeded(const RenderStyle* renderStyle)
489{
490 // If a node's text fill color is invalid, then its children use
491 // their font-color as their text fill color (they don't
492 // inherit it). Likewise for stroke color.
493 if (!renderStyle->textFillColor().isValid())
494 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitTextFillColor);
495 if (!renderStyle->textStrokeColor().isValid())
496 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitTextStrokeColor);
497}

499void EditingStyle::setProperty(CSSPropertyID propertyID, const String& value, bool important)
500{
501 if (!m_mutableStyle)
502 m_mutableStyle = MutableStyleProperties::create();
503
504 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(propertyID, value, important);
505}
506
507void EditingStyle::extractFontSizeDelta()
508{
509 if (!m_mutableStyle)
510 return;
511
512 if (m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyFontSize)) {
513 // Explicit font size overrides any delta.
514 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitFontSizeDelta);
515 return;
516 }
517
518 // Get the adjustment amount out of the style.
519 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitFontSizeDelta);
520 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value))
521 return;
522
523 CSSPrimitiveValue& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value);
524
525 // Only PX handled now. If we handle more types in the future, perhaps
526 // a switch statement here would be more appropriate.
527 if (!primitiveValue.isPx())
528 return;
529
530 m_fontSizeDelta = primitiveValue.floatValue();
531 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitFontSizeDelta);
532}
533
534bool EditingStyle::isEmpty() const
535{
536 return (!m_mutableStyle || m_mutableStyle->isEmpty()) && m_fontSizeDelta == NoFontDelta
537 && underlineChange() == TextDecorationChange::None && strikeThroughChange() == TextDecorationChange::None;
538}
539
540Ref<MutableStyleProperties> EditingStyle::styleWithResolvedTextDecorations() const
541{
542 bool hasTextDecorationChanges = underlineChange() != TextDecorationChange::None || strikeThroughChange() != TextDecorationChange::None;
543 if (m_mutableStyle && !hasTextDecorationChanges)
544 return *m_mutableStyle;
545
546 Ref<MutableStyleProperties> style = m_mutableStyle ? m_mutableStyle->mutableCopy() : MutableStyleProperties::create();
547
548 Ref<CSSValueList> valueList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
549 if (underlineChange() == TextDecorationChange::Add)
550 valueList->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline));
551 if (strikeThroughChange() == TextDecorationChange::Add)
552 valueList->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough));
553
554 if (valueList->length())
555 style->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, valueList.ptr());
556 else
557 style->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone));
558
559 return style;
560}
561
562std::optional<WritingDirection> EditingStyle::textDirection() const
563{
564 if (!m_mutableStyle)
565 return std::nullopt;
566
567 RefPtr<CSSValue> unicodeBidi = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi);
568 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(unicodeBidi))
569 return std::nullopt;
570
571 CSSValueID unicodeBidiValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*unicodeBidi).valueID();
572 if (unicodeBidiValue == CSSValueEmbed) {
573 RefPtr<CSSValue> direction = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyDirection);
574 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(direction))
575 return std::nullopt;
576
577 return downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*direction).valueID() == CSSValueLtr ? WritingDirection::LeftToRight : WritingDirection::RightToLeft;
578 }
579
580 if (unicodeBidiValue == CSSValueNormal)
581 return WritingDirection::Natural;
582
583 return std::nullopt;
584}

586void EditingStyle::setStyle(RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties>&& style)
587{
588 m_mutableStyle = WTFMove(style);
589 // FIXME: We should be able to figure out whether or not font is fixed width for mutable style.
590 // We need to check font-family is monospace as in FontDescription but we don't want to duplicate code here.
591 m_shouldUseFixedDefaultFontSize = false;
592 extractFontSizeDelta();
593}

595void EditingStyle::overrideWithStyle(const StyleProperties& style)
596{
597 return mergeStyle(&style, OverrideValues);
598}
599
600static void applyTextDecorationChangeToValueList(CSSValueList& valueList, TextDecorationChange change, Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue>&& value)
601{
602 switch (change) {
603 case TextDecorationChange::None:
604 break;
605 case TextDecorationChange::Add:
606 valueList.append(WTFMove(value));
607 break;
608 case TextDecorationChange::Remove:
609 valueList.removeAll(&value.get());
610 break;
611 }
612}
613
614void EditingStyle::overrideTypingStyleAt(const EditingStyle& style, const Position& position)
615{
616 mergeStyle(style.m_mutableStyle.get(), OverrideValues);
617
618 m_fontSizeDelta += style.m_fontSizeDelta;
619
620 prepareToApplyAt(position, EditingStyle::PreserveWritingDirection);
621
622 auto underlineChange = style.underlineChange();
623 auto strikeThroughChange = style.strikeThroughChange();
624 if (underlineChange == TextDecorationChange::None && strikeThroughChange == TextDecorationChange::None)
625 return;
626
627 if (!m_mutableStyle)
628 m_mutableStyle = MutableStyleProperties::create();
629
630 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
631 Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> underline = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline);
632 Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineThrough = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough);
633 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
634 RefPtr<CSSValueList> valueList;
635 if (value && value->isValueList()) {
636 valueList = downcast<CSSValueList>(*value).copy();
637 applyTextDecorationChangeToValueList(*valueList, underlineChange, WTFMove(underline));
638 applyTextDecorationChangeToValueList(*valueList, strikeThroughChange, WTFMove(lineThrough));
639 } else {
640 valueList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
641 if (underlineChange == TextDecorationChange::Add)
642 valueList->append(WTFMove(underline));
643 if (strikeThroughChange == TextDecorationChange::Add)
644 valueList->append(WTFMove(lineThrough));
645 }
646 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect, valueList.get());
647}
648
649void EditingStyle::clear()
650{
651 m_mutableStyle = nullptr;
652 m_shouldUseFixedDefaultFontSize = false;
653 m_fontSizeDelta = NoFontDelta;
654 setUnderlineChange(TextDecorationChange::None);
655 setStrikeThroughChange(TextDecorationChange::None);
656}
657
658Ref<EditingStyle> EditingStyle::copy() const
659{
660 auto copy = EditingStyle::create();
661 if (m_mutableStyle)
662 copy->m_mutableStyle = m_mutableStyle->mutableCopy();
663 copy->m_shouldUseFixedDefaultFontSize = m_shouldUseFixedDefaultFontSize;
664 copy->m_underlineChange = m_underlineChange;
665 copy->m_strikeThroughChange = m_strikeThroughChange;
666 copy->m_fontSizeDelta = m_fontSizeDelta;
667 return copy;
668}

670Ref<EditingStyle> EditingStyle::extractAndRemoveBlockProperties()
671{
672 auto blockProperties = EditingStyle::create();
673 if (!m_mutableStyle)
674 return blockProperties;
675
676 blockProperties->m_mutableStyle = m_mutableStyle->copyBlockProperties();
677 m_mutableStyle->removeBlockProperties();
678
679 return blockProperties;
680}
681
682Ref<EditingStyle> EditingStyle::extractAndRemoveTextDirection()
683{
684 auto textDirection = EditingStyle::create();
685 textDirection->m_mutableStyle = MutableStyleProperties::create();
686 textDirection->m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi, CSSValueEmbed, m_mutableStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi));
687 textDirection->m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyDirection, m_mutableStyle->getPropertyValue(CSSPropertyDirection),
688 m_mutableStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyDirection));
689
690 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi);
691 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyDirection);
692
693 return textDirection;
694}

704void EditingStyle::removeStyleAddedByNode(Node* node)
705{
706 if (!node || !node->parentNode())
707 return;
708 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> parentStyle = copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(node->parentNode(), EditingPropertiesInEffect);
709 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> nodeStyle = copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(node, EditingPropertiesInEffect);

711 removeEquivalentProperties(*nodeStyle);

714void EditingStyle::removeStyleConflictingWithStyleOfNode(Node& node)
715{
716 if (!node.parentNode() || !m_mutableStyle)
717 return;
718
719 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> parentStyle = copyPropertiesFromComputedStyle(node.parentNode(), EditingPropertiesInEffect);
720 auto nodeStyle = EditingStyle::create(&node, EditingPropertiesInEffect);
721 nodeStyle->removeEquivalentProperties(*parentStyle);
722
723 MutableStyleProperties* style = nodeStyle->style();
724 unsigned propertyCount = style->propertyCount();
725 for (unsigned i = 0; i < propertyCount; ++i)
726 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(style->propertyAt(i).id());

729void EditingStyle::collapseTextDecorationProperties()
730{
731 if (!m_mutableStyle)
732 return;
733
734 RefPtr<CSSValue> textDecorationsInEffect = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
735 if (!textDecorationsInEffect)
736 return;
737
738 if (textDecorationsInEffect->isValueList())
739 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, textDecorationsInEffect->cssText(), m_mutableStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyTextDecoration));
740 else
741 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
742 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
743}
744
745// CSS properties that create a visual difference only when applied to text.
746static const CSSPropertyID textOnlyProperties[] = {
747 CSSPropertyTextDecoration,
748 CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect,
749 CSSPropertyFontStyle,
750 CSSPropertyFontWeight,
751 CSSPropertyColor,
752};
753
754TriState EditingStyle::triStateOfStyle(EditingStyle* style) const
755{
756 if (!style || !style->m_mutableStyle)
757 return TriState::False;
758 return triStateOfStyle(*style->m_mutableStyle, DoNotIgnoreTextOnlyProperties);
759}
760
761template<typename T>
762TriState EditingStyle::triStateOfStyle(T& styleToCompare, ShouldIgnoreTextOnlyProperties shouldIgnoreTextOnlyProperties) const
763{
764 if (!m_mutableStyle)
765 return TriState::True;
766
767 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> difference = getPropertiesNotIn(*m_mutableStyle, styleToCompare);
768
769 if (shouldIgnoreTextOnlyProperties == IgnoreTextOnlyProperties)
770 difference->removePropertiesInSet(textOnlyProperties, WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(textOnlyProperties));
771
772 if (difference->isEmpty())
773 return TriState::True;
774 if (difference->propertyCount() == m_mutableStyle->propertyCount())
775 return TriState::False;
776
777 return TriState::Indeterminate;
778}
779
780TriState EditingStyle::triStateOfStyle(const VisibleSelection& selection) const
781{
782 if (!selection.isCaretOrRange())
783 return TriState::False;
784
785 if (selection.isCaret())
786 return triStateOfStyle(EditingStyle::styleAtSelectionStart(selection).get());
787
788 TriState state = TriState::False;
789 bool nodeIsStart = true;
790 for (Node* node = selection.start().deprecatedNode(); node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node)) {
791 if (node->renderer() && node->hasEditableStyle()) {
792 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyle(node);
793 TriState nodeState = triStateOfStyle(computedStyle, node->isTextNode() ? EditingStyle::DoNotIgnoreTextOnlyProperties : EditingStyle::IgnoreTextOnlyProperties);
794 if (nodeIsStart) {
795 state = nodeState;
796 nodeIsStart = false;
797 } else if (state != nodeState && node->isTextNode()) {
798 state = TriState::Indeterminate;
799 break;
800 }
801 }
802
803 if (node == selection.end().deprecatedNode())
804 break;
805 }
806
807 return state;
808}

810static RefPtr<CSSValueList> textDecorationValueList(const StyleProperties& properties)
811{
812 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = properties.getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
813 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value))
814 return nullptr;
815 return downcast<CSSValueList>(value.get());
816}
817
818bool EditingStyle::conflictsWithInlineStyleOfElement(StyledElement& element, RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties>* newInlineStylePtr, EditingStyle* extractedStyle) const
819{
820 const StyleProperties* inlineStyle = element.inlineStyle();
821 if (!inlineStyle)
822 return false;
823 bool conflicts = false;
824 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> newInlineStyle;
825 if (newInlineStylePtr) {
826 newInlineStyle = inlineStyle->mutableCopy();
827 *newInlineStylePtr = newInlineStyle;
828 }
829
830 bool shouldRemoveUnderline = underlineChange() == TextDecorationChange::Remove;
831 bool shouldRemoveStrikeThrough = strikeThroughChange() == TextDecorationChange::Remove;
832 if (shouldRemoveUnderline || shouldRemoveStrikeThrough) {
833 if (RefPtr<CSSValueList> valueList = textDecorationValueList(*inlineStyle)) {
834 auto newValueList = valueList->copy();
835 auto extractedValueList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
836
837 Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> underline = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline);
838 if (shouldRemoveUnderline && valueList->hasValue(underline.ptr())) {
839 if (!newInlineStyle)
840 return true;
841 newValueList->removeAll(underline.ptr());
842 extractedValueList->append(WTFMove(underline));
843 }
844
845 Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineThrough = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough);
846 if (shouldRemoveStrikeThrough && valueList->hasValue(lineThrough.ptr())) {
847 if (!newInlineStyle)
848 return true;
849 newValueList->removeAll(lineThrough.ptr());
850 extractedValueList->append(WTFMove(lineThrough));
851 }
852
853 if (extractedValueList->length()) {
854 conflicts = true;
855 if (newValueList->length())
856 newInlineStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, WTFMove(newValueList));
857 else
858 newInlineStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
859
860 if (extractedStyle) {
861 bool isImportant = inlineStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
862 extractedStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, extractedValueList->cssText(), isImportant);
863 }
864 }
865 }
866 }
867
868 unsigned propertyCount = m_mutableStyle ? m_mutableStyle->propertyCount() : 0;
869 for (unsigned i = 0; i < propertyCount; ++i) {
870 CSSPropertyID propertyID = m_mutableStyle->propertyAt(i).id();
871
872 // We don't override whitespace property of a tab span because that would collapse the tab into a space.
873 if (propertyID == CSSPropertyWhiteSpace && isTabSpanNode(&element))
874 continue;
875
876 if (propertyID == CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect && inlineStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration)) {
877 if (!newInlineStyle)
878 return true;
879 conflicts = true;
880 newInlineStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
881 if (extractedStyle)
882 extractedStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, inlineStyle->getPropertyValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration), inlineStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyTextDecoration));
883 }
884
885 if (!inlineStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(propertyID))
886 continue;
887
888 if (propertyID == CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi && inlineStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyDirection)) {
889 if (!newInlineStyle)
890 return true;
891 conflicts = true;
892 newInlineStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyDirection);
893 if (extractedStyle)
894 extractedStyle->setProperty(propertyID, inlineStyle->getPropertyValue(propertyID), inlineStyle->propertyIsImportant(propertyID));
895 }
896
897 if (!newInlineStyle)
898 return true;
899
900 conflicts = true;
901 newInlineStyle->removeProperty(propertyID);
902 if (extractedStyle)
903 extractedStyle->setProperty(propertyID, inlineStyle->getPropertyValue(propertyID), inlineStyle->propertyIsImportant(propertyID));
904 }
905
906 return conflicts;
907}

928{

930 return false;

970
971bool EditingStyle::extractConflictingImplicitStyleOfAttributes(HTMLElement& element, ShouldPreserveWritingDirection shouldPreserveWritingDirection,
972 EditingStyle* extractedStyle, Vector<QualifiedName>& conflictingAttributes, ShouldExtractMatchingStyle shouldExtractMatchingStyle) const
973{
974 // HTMLAttributeEquivalent::addToStyle doesn't support unicode-bidi and direction properties
975 ASSERT(!extractedStyle || shouldPreserveWritingDirection == PreserveWritingDirection);
976 if (!m_mutableStyle)
977 return false;
978
979 bool removed = false;
980 for (auto& equivalent : htmlAttributeEquivalents()) {
981 // unicode-bidi and direction are pushed down separately so don't push down with other styles.
982 if (shouldPreserveWritingDirection == PreserveWritingDirection && equivalent->attributeName() == HTMLNames::dirAttr)
983 continue;
984
985 if (!equivalent->matches(element) || !equivalent->propertyExistsInStyle(*this)
986 || (shouldExtractMatchingStyle == DoNotExtractMatchingStyle && equivalent->valueIsPresentInStyle(element, *this)))
987 continue;
988
989 if (extractedStyle)
990 equivalent->addToStyle(&element, extractedStyle);
991 conflictingAttributes.append(equivalent->attributeName());
992 removed = true;
993 }
994
995 return removed;
996}
997
998bool EditingStyle::styleIsPresentInComputedStyleOfNode(Node& node) const
999{
1000 if (isEmpty())
1001 return true;
1002 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyle(&node);
1003
1004 bool shouldAddUnderline = underlineChange() == TextDecorationChange::Add;
1005 bool shouldAddLineThrough = strikeThroughChange() == TextDecorationChange::Add;
1006 if (shouldAddUnderline || shouldAddLineThrough) {
1007 bool hasUnderline = false;
1008 bool hasLineThrough = false;
1009 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> value = computedStyle.propertyValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration)) {
1010 if (value->isValueList()) {
1011 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1012 const CSSValueList& valueList = downcast<CSSValueList>(*value);
1013 hasUnderline = valueList.hasValue(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline).ptr());
1014 hasLineThrough = valueList.hasValue(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough).ptr());
1015 }
1016 }
1017 if ((shouldAddUnderline && !hasUnderline) || (shouldAddLineThrough && !hasLineThrough))
1018 return false;
1019 }
1020
1021 return !m_mutableStyle || getPropertiesNotIn(*m_mutableStyle, computedStyle)->isEmpty();
1022}
1023
1024bool EditingStyle::elementIsStyledSpanOrHTMLEquivalent(const HTMLElement& element)
1025{
1026 bool elementIsSpanOrElementEquivalent = false;
1027 if (element.hasTagName(HTMLNames::spanTag))
1028 elementIsSpanOrElementEquivalent = true;
1029 else {
1030 for (auto& equivalent : htmlElementEquivalents()) {
1031 if (equivalent->matches(element)) {
1032 elementIsSpanOrElementEquivalent = true;
1033 break;
1034 }
1035 }
1036 }
1037
1038 if (!element.hasAttributes())
1039 return elementIsSpanOrElementEquivalent; // span, b, etc... without any attributes
1040
1041 unsigned matchedAttributes = 0;
1042 for (auto& equivalent : htmlAttributeEquivalents()) {
1043 if (equivalent->matches(element) && equivalent->attributeName() != HTMLNames::dirAttr)
1044 matchedAttributes++;
1045 }
1046
1047 if (!elementIsSpanOrElementEquivalent && !matchedAttributes)
1048 return false; // element is not a span, a html element equivalent, or font element.
1049
1050 if (element.attributeWithoutSynchronization(HTMLNames::classAttr) == AppleStyleSpanClass)
1051 matchedAttributes++;
1052
1053 if (element.hasAttribute(HTMLNames::styleAttr)) {
1054 if (const StyleProperties* style = element.inlineStyle()) {
1055 unsigned propertyCount = style->propertyCount();
1056 for (unsigned i = 0; i < propertyCount; ++i) {
1057 if (!isEditingProperty(style->propertyAt(i).id()))
1058 return false;
1059 }
1060 }
1061 matchedAttributes++;
1062 }
1063
1064 // font with color attribute, span with style attribute, etc...
1065 ASSERT(matchedAttributes <= element.attributeCount());
1066 return matchedAttributes >= element.attributeCount();
1067}
1068
1069void EditingStyle::prepareToApplyAt(const Position& position, ShouldPreserveWritingDirection shouldPreserveWritingDirection)
1070{
1071 if (!m_mutableStyle)
1072 return;
1073
1074 // ReplaceSelectionCommand::handleStyleSpans() requires that this function only removes the editing style.
1075 // If this function was modified in the future to delete all redundant properties, then add a boolean value to indicate
1076 // which one of editingStyleAtPosition or computedStyle is called.
1077 auto editingStyleAtPosition = EditingStyle::create(position, EditingPropertiesInEffect);
1078 StyleProperties* styleAtPosition = editingStyleAtPosition->m_mutableStyle.get();
1079
1080 RefPtr<CSSValue> unicodeBidi;
1081 RefPtr<CSSValue> direction;
1082 if (shouldPreserveWritingDirection == PreserveWritingDirection) {
1083 unicodeBidi = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi);
1084 direction = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyDirection);
1085 }
1086
1087 removeEquivalentProperties(*styleAtPosition);
1088
1089 if (textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(*m_mutableStyle) == textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(*styleAtPosition))
1090 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyTextAlign);
1091
1092 if (equalIgnoringSemanticColor(textColorFromStyle(*m_mutableStyle), textColorFromStyle(*styleAtPosition)))
1093 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyColor);
1094
1095 if (equalIgnoringSemanticColor(caretColorFromStyle(*m_mutableStyle), caretColorFromStyle(*styleAtPosition)))
1096 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1097
1098 if (hasTransparentBackgroundColor(m_mutableStyle.get())
1099 || cssValueToColor(m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor).get()) == rgbaBackgroundColorInEffect(position.containerNode()))
1100 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1101
1102 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(unicodeBidi)) {
1103 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi, static_cast<CSSValueID>(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*unicodeBidi).valueID()));
1104 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(direction))
1105 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyDirection, static_cast<CSSValueID>(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*direction).valueID()));
1106 }
1107}

1112 if (!typingStyle || typingStyle == this)

1118void EditingStyle::mergeInlineStyleOfElement(StyledElement& element, CSSPropertyOverrideMode mode, PropertiesToInclude propertiesToInclude)
1119{
1120 if (!element.inlineStyle())
1121 return;
1122
1123 switch (propertiesToInclude) {
1124 case AllProperties:
1125 mergeStyle(element.inlineStyle(), mode);
1126 return;
1127 case OnlyEditingInheritableProperties:
1128 mergeStyle(copyEditingProperties(element.inlineStyle(), OnlyInheritableEditingProperties).ptr(), mode);
1129 return;
1130 case EditingPropertiesInEffect:
1131 mergeStyle(copyEditingProperties(element.inlineStyle(), AllEditingProperties).ptr(), mode);
1132 return;
1133 }
1134}

1136static inline bool elementMatchesAndPropertyIsNotInInlineStyleDecl(const HTMLElementEquivalent& equivalent, const StyledElement& element,
1137 EditingStyle::CSSPropertyOverrideMode mode, EditingStyle& style)
1138{
1139 if (!equivalent.matches(element))
1140 return false;
1141 if (mode != EditingStyle::OverrideValues && equivalent.propertyExistsInStyle(style))
1142 return false;
1143
1144 return !element.inlineStyle() || !equivalent.propertyExistsInStyle(EditingStyle::create(element.inlineStyle()).get());
1145}

1147static RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> extractEditingProperties(const StyleProperties* style, EditingStyle::PropertiesToInclude propertiesToInclude)
1148{
1149 if (!style)
1150 return nullptr;
1151
1152 switch (propertiesToInclude) {
1153 case EditingStyle::OnlyEditingInheritableProperties:
1154 return copyEditingProperties(style, OnlyInheritableEditingProperties);
1155 case EditingStyle::AllProperties:
1156 case EditingStyle::EditingPropertiesInEffect:
1157 break;
1158 }
1159 return copyEditingProperties(style, AllEditingProperties);
1160}
1161
1162void EditingStyle::mergeInlineAndImplicitStyleOfElement(StyledElement& element, CSSPropertyOverrideMode mode, PropertiesToInclude propertiesToInclude, StandardFontFamilySerializationMode standardFontFamilySerializationMode)
1163{
1164 auto styleFromRules = EditingStyle::create();
1165 styleFromRules->mergeStyleFromRulesForSerialization(element, standardFontFamilySerializationMode);
1166
1167 if (element.inlineStyle())
1168 styleFromRules->m_mutableStyle->mergeAndOverrideOnConflict(*element.inlineStyle());
1169
1170 styleFromRules->m_mutableStyle = extractEditingProperties(styleFromRules->m_mutableStyle.get(), propertiesToInclude);
1171 mergeStyle(styleFromRules->m_mutableStyle.get(), mode);
1172
1173 for (auto& equivalent : htmlElementEquivalents()) {
1174 if (elementMatchesAndPropertyIsNotInInlineStyleDecl(*equivalent, element, mode, *this))
1175 equivalent->addToStyle(&element, this);
1176 }
1177
1178 for (auto& equivalent : htmlAttributeEquivalents()) {
1179 if (equivalent->attributeName() == HTMLNames::dirAttr)
1180 continue; // We don't want to include directionality
1181 if (elementMatchesAndPropertyIsNotInInlineStyleDecl(*equivalent, element, mode, *this))
1182 equivalent->addToStyle(&element, this);
1183 }
1184}
1185
1186Ref<EditingStyle> EditingStyle::wrappingStyleForSerialization(Node& context, bool shouldAnnotate, StandardFontFamilySerializationMode standardFontFamilySerializationMode)
1187{
1188 if (shouldAnnotate) {
1189 auto wrappingStyle = EditingStyle::create(&context, EditingStyle::EditingPropertiesInEffect);
1190
1191 // Styles that Mail blockquotes contribute should only be placed on the Mail blockquote,
1192 // to help us differentiate those styles from ones that the user has applied.
1193 // This helps us get the color of content pasted into blockquotes right.
1194 wrappingStyle->removeStyleAddedByNode(enclosingNodeOfType(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(&context), isMailBlockquote, CanCrossEditingBoundary));
1195
1196 // Call collapseTextDecorationProperties first or otherwise it'll copy the value over from in-effect to text-decorations.
1197 wrappingStyle->collapseTextDecorationProperties();
1198
1199 return wrappingStyle;
1200 }
1201
1202 auto wrappingStyle = EditingStyle::create();
1203
1204 // When not annotating for interchange, we only preserve inline style declarations.
1205 for (Node* node = &context; node && !node->isDocumentNode(); node = node->parentNode()) {
1206 if (is<StyledElement>(*node) && !isMailBlockquote(node))
1207 wrappingStyle->mergeInlineAndImplicitStyleOfElement(downcast<StyledElement>(*node), DoNotOverrideValues, EditingPropertiesInEffect, standardFontFamilySerializationMode);
1208 }
1209
1210 return wrappingStyle;
1211}

1214static void mergeTextDecorationValues(CSSValueList& mergedValue, const CSSValueList& valueToMerge)
1215{
1216 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1217 Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> underline = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline);
1218 Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineThrough = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough);
1219
1220 if (valueToMerge.hasValue(underline.ptr()) && !mergedValue.hasValue(underline.ptr()))
1221 mergedValue.append(WTFMove(underline));
1222
1223 if (valueToMerge.hasValue(lineThrough.ptr()) && !mergedValue.hasValue(lineThrough.ptr()))
1224 mergedValue.append(WTFMove(lineThrough));
1225}
1226
1227void EditingStyle::mergeStyle(const StyleProperties* style, CSSPropertyOverrideMode mode)
1228{
1229 if (!style)
1230 return;
1231
1232 if (!m_mutableStyle) {
1233 m_mutableStyle = style->mutableCopy();
1234 return;
1235 }
1236
1237 unsigned propertyCount = style->propertyCount();
1238 for (unsigned i = 0; i < propertyCount; ++i) {
1239 StyleProperties::PropertyReference property = style->propertyAt(i);
1240 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(property.id());
1241
1242 // text decorations never override values.
1243 if ((property.id() == CSSPropertyTextDecoration || property.id() == CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect)
1244 && is<CSSValueList>(*property.value()) && value) {
1245 if (is<CSSValueList>(*value)) {
1246 auto newValue = downcast<CSSValueList>(*value).copy();
1247 mergeTextDecorationValues(newValue, downcast<CSSValueList>(*property.value()));
1248 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(property.id(), WTFMove(newValue), property.isImportant());
1249 continue;
1250 }
1251 value = nullptr; // text-decoration: none is equivalent to not having the property.
1252 }
1253
1254 if (mode == OverrideValues || (mode == DoNotOverrideValues && !value))
1255 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(property.id(), property.value(), property.isImportant());
1256 }
1257
1258 int oldFontSizeDelta = m_fontSizeDelta;
1259 extractFontSizeDelta();
1260 m_fontSizeDelta += oldFontSizeDelta;
1261}
1262
1263static Ref<MutableStyleProperties> styleFromMatchedRulesForElement(Element& element, unsigned rulesToInclude)
1264{
1265 auto style = MutableStyleProperties::create();
1266 for (auto& matchedRule : element.styleResolver().styleRulesForElement(&element, rulesToInclude))
1267 style->mergeAndOverrideOnConflict(matchedRule->properties());
1268
1269 return style;
1270}
1271
1272void EditingStyle::mergeStyleFromRules(StyledElement& element)
1273{
1274 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> styleFromMatchedRules = styleFromMatchedRulesForElement(element,
1275 Style::Resolver::AuthorCSSRules);
1276 // Styles from the inline style declaration, held in the variable "style", take precedence
1277 // over those from matched rules.
1278 if (m_mutableStyle)
1279 styleFromMatchedRules->mergeAndOverrideOnConflict(*m_mutableStyle);
1280
1281 clear();
1282 m_mutableStyle = styleFromMatchedRules;
1283}

1286{
1287 if (!primitiveValue.isFontFamily())
1288 return { };

1291
1292static String loneFontFamilyName(const CSSValue& value)
1293{
1294 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value))
1295 return familyNameFromCSSPrimitiveValue(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value));
1296
1297 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value) || downcast<CSSValueList>(value).length() != 1)
1298 return { };
1299
1300 auto& item = *downcast<CSSValueList>(value).item(0);
1301 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item))
1302 return { };
1303
1304 return familyNameFromCSSPrimitiveValue(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item));
1305}
1306
1307void EditingStyle::mergeStyleFromRulesForSerialization(StyledElement& element, StandardFontFamilySerializationMode standardFontFamilySerializationMode)
1308{
1309 mergeStyleFromRules(element);
1310
1311 // The property value, if it's a percentage, may not reflect the actual computed value.
1312 // For example: style="height: 1%; overflow: visible;" in quirksmode
1313 // FIXME: There are others like this, see <rdar://problem/5195123> Slashdot copy/paste fidelity problem
1314 auto fromComputedStyle = MutableStyleProperties::create();
1315 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyle(&element);
1316
1317 bool shouldRemoveFontFamily = false;
1318 {
1319 unsigned propertyCount = m_mutableStyle->propertyCount();
1320 for (unsigned i = 0; i < propertyCount; ++i) {
1321 StyleProperties::PropertyReference property = m_mutableStyle->propertyAt(i);
1322 CSSValue& value = *property.value();
1323 if (property.id() == CSSPropertyFontFamily) {
1324 auto familyName = loneFontFamilyName(value);
1325 if (FontCache::isSystemFontForbiddenForEditing(familyName)
1326 || (standardFontFamilySerializationMode == StandardFontFamilySerializationMode::Strip && familyName == standardFamily))
1327 shouldRemoveFontFamily = true;
1328 continue;
1329 }
1330 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value))
1331 continue;
1332 if (downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).isPercentage()) {
1333 if (auto computedPropertyValue = computedStyle.propertyValue(property.id()))
1334 fromComputedStyle->addParsedProperty(CSSProperty(property.id(), WTFMove(computedPropertyValue)));
1335 }
1336 }
1337 }
1338 if (shouldRemoveFontFamily) {
1339 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontFamily);
1340 fromComputedStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontFamily);
1341 }
1342 m_mutableStyle->mergeAndOverrideOnConflict(fromComputedStyle.get());
1343}
1344
1345static void removePropertiesInStyle(MutableStyleProperties* styleToRemovePropertiesFrom, MutableStyleProperties* style)
1346{
1347 unsigned propertyCount = style->propertyCount();
1348 Vector<CSSPropertyID> propertiesToRemove(propertyCount);
1349 for (unsigned i = 0; i < propertyCount; ++i)
1350 propertiesToRemove[i] = style->propertyAt(i).id();
1351
1352 styleToRemovePropertiesFrom->removePropertiesInSet(propertiesToRemove.data(), propertiesToRemove.size());
1353}
1354
1355void EditingStyle::removeStyleFromRulesAndContext(StyledElement& element, Node* context)
1356{
1357 if (!m_mutableStyle)
1358 return;
1359
1360 // 1. Remove style from matched rules because style remain without repeating it in inline style declaration
1361 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> styleFromMatchedRules = styleFromMatchedRulesForElement(element, Style::Resolver::AllButEmptyCSSRules);
1362 if (styleFromMatchedRules && !styleFromMatchedRules->isEmpty())
1363 m_mutableStyle = getPropertiesNotIn(*m_mutableStyle, *styleFromMatchedRules);
1364
1365 // 2. Remove style present in context and not overridden by matched rules.
1366 auto computedStyle = EditingStyle::create(context, EditingPropertiesInEffect);
1367 if (computedStyle->m_mutableStyle) {
1368 if (!computedStyle->m_mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor))
1369 computedStyle->m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor, CSSValueTransparent);
1370
1371 RefPtr<EditingStyle> computedStyleOfElement;
1372 auto replaceSemanticColorWithComputedValue = [&](const CSSPropertyID id) {
1373 auto color = m_mutableStyle->propertyAsColor(id);
1374 if (!color || (color->isVisible() && !color->isSemantic()))
1375 return;
1376
1377 if (!computedStyleOfElement)
1378 computedStyleOfElement = EditingStyle::create(&element, EditingPropertiesInEffect);
1379
1380 if (!computedStyleOfElement->m_mutableStyle)
1381 return;
1382
1383 auto computedValue = computedStyleOfElement->m_mutableStyle->getPropertyValue(id);
1384 if (!computedValue)
1385 return;
1386
1387 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(id, computedValue);
1388 };
1389
1390 // Replace semantic color identifiers like -apple-system-label with RGB values so that comparsions in getPropertiesNotIn below would work.
1391 replaceSemanticColorWithComputedValue(CSSPropertyColor);
1392 replaceSemanticColorWithComputedValue(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1393 replaceSemanticColorWithComputedValue(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1394
1395 removePropertiesInStyle(computedStyle->m_mutableStyle.get(), styleFromMatchedRules.get());
1396 m_mutableStyle = getPropertiesNotIn(*m_mutableStyle, *computedStyle->m_mutableStyle);
1397 }
1398
1399 // 3. If this element is a span and has display: inline or float: none, remove them unless they are overridden by rules.
1400 // These rules are added by serialization code to wrap text nodes.
1401 if (isStyleSpanOrSpanWithOnlyStyleAttribute(element)) {
1402 if (!styleFromMatchedRules->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyDisplay) && identifierForStyleProperty(*m_mutableStyle, CSSPropertyDisplay) == CSSValueInline)
1403 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyDisplay);
1404 if (!styleFromMatchedRules->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyFloat) && identifierForStyleProperty(*m_mutableStyle, CSSPropertyFloat) == CSSValueNone)
1405 m_mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyFloat);
1406 }
1407}
1408
1409void EditingStyle::removePropertiesInElementDefaultStyle(Element& element)
1410{
1411 if (!m_mutableStyle || m_mutableStyle->isEmpty())
1412 return;
1413
1414 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> defaultStyle = styleFromMatchedRulesForElement(element, Style::Resolver::UAAndUserCSSRules);
1415
1416 removePropertiesInStyle(m_mutableStyle.get(), defaultStyle.get());
1417}

1447bool EditingStyle::convertPositionStyle()
1448{
1449 if (!m_mutableStyle)
1450 return false;
1451
1452 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1453 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> sticky = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueSticky);
1454 if (m_mutableStyle->propertyMatches(CSSPropertyPosition, sticky.get())) {
1455 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyPosition, cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueStatic), m_mutableStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyPosition));
1456 return false;
1457 }
1458 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> fixed = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueFixed);
1459 if (m_mutableStyle->propertyMatches(CSSPropertyPosition, fixed.get())) {
1460 m_mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyPosition, cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAbsolute), m_mutableStyle->propertyIsImportant(CSSPropertyPosition));
1461 return true;
1462 }
1463 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> absolute = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAbsolute);
1464 if (m_mutableStyle->propertyMatches(CSSPropertyPosition, absolute.get()))
1465 return true;
1466 return false;
1467}

1489
1490RefPtr<EditingStyle> EditingStyle::styleAtSelectionStart(const VisibleSelection& selection, bool shouldUseBackgroundColorInEffect)
1491{
1492 if (selection.isNone())
1493 return nullptr;
1494
1495 Position position = adjustedSelectionStartForStyleComputation(selection);
1496
1497 // If the pos is at the end of a text node, then this node is not fully selected.
1498 // Move it to the next deep equivalent position to avoid removing the style from this node.
1499 // e.g. if pos was at Position("hello", 5) in <b>hello<div>world</div></b>, we want Position("world", 0) instead.
1500 // We only do this for range because caret at Position("hello", 5) in <b>hello</b>world should give you font-weight: bold.
1501 Node* positionNode = position.containerNode();
1502 if (selection.isRange() && is<Text>(positionNode) && static_cast<unsigned>(position.computeOffsetInContainerNode()) == downcast<Text>(*positionNode).length())
1503 position = nextVisuallyDistinctCandidate(position);
1504
1505 Element* element = position.element();
1506 if (!element)
1507 return nullptr;
1508
1509 auto style = EditingStyle::create(element, EditingStyle::AllProperties);
1510 style->mergeTypingStyle(element->document());
1511
1512 // If background color is transparent, traverse parent nodes until we hit a different value or document root
1513 // Also, if the selection is a range, ignore the background color at the start of selection,
1514 // and find the background color of the common ancestor.
1515 if (shouldUseBackgroundColorInEffect && (selection.isRange() || hasTransparentBackgroundColor(style->m_mutableStyle.get()))) {
1516 if (auto range = selection.toNormalizedRange()) {
1517 if (auto value = backgroundColorInEffect(commonInclusiveAncestor<ComposedTree>(*range)))
1518 style->setProperty(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor, value->cssText());
1519 }
1520 }
1521
1522 return style;
1523}
1524
1525WritingDirection EditingStyle::textDirectionForSelection(const VisibleSelection& selection, EditingStyle* typingStyle, bool& hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings)
1526{
1527 hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings = true;
1528
1529 if (selection.isNone())
1530 return WritingDirection::Natural;
1531
1532 Position position = selection.start().downstream();
1533
1534 Node* node = position.deprecatedNode();
1535 if (!node)
1536 return WritingDirection::Natural;
1537
1538 Position end;
1539 if (selection.isRange()) {
1540 end = selection.end().upstream();
1541 for (auto& intersectingNode : intersectingNodes(*makeSimpleRange(position, end))) {
1542 if (!intersectingNode.isStyledElement())
1543 continue;
1544 auto valueObject = ComputedStyleExtractor(&intersectingNode).propertyValue(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi);
1545 auto value = is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(valueObject) ? downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*valueObject).valueID() : CSSValueInvalid;
1546 if (value == CSSValueEmbed || value == CSSValueBidiOverride)
1547 return WritingDirection::Natural;
1548 }
1549 }
1550
1551 if (selection.isCaret()) {
1552 if (typingStyle) {
1553 if (auto direction = typingStyle->textDirection()) {
1554 hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings = false;
1555 return *direction;
1556 }
1557 }
1558 node = selection.visibleStart().deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode();
1559 }
1560
1561 // The selection is either a caret with no typing attributes or a range in which no embedding is added, so just use the start position
1562 // to decide.
1563 Node* block = enclosingBlock(node);
1564 auto foundDirection = WritingDirection::Natural;
1565
1566 for (; node != block; node = node->parentNode()) {
1567 if (!node->isStyledElement())
1568 continue;
1569
1570 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyle(node);
1571 RefPtr<CSSValue> unicodeBidi = computedStyle.propertyValue(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi);
1572 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(unicodeBidi))
1573 continue;
1574
1575 CSSValueID unicodeBidiValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*unicodeBidi).valueID();
1576 if (unicodeBidiValue == CSSValueNormal)
1577 continue;
1578
1579 if (unicodeBidiValue == CSSValueBidiOverride)
1580 return WritingDirection::Natural;
1581
1582 ASSERT(unicodeBidiValue == CSSValueEmbed);
1583 RefPtr<CSSValue> direction = computedStyle.propertyValue(CSSPropertyDirection);
1584 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(direction))
1585 continue;
1586
1587 CSSValueID directionValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*direction).valueID();
1588 if (directionValue != CSSValueLtr && directionValue != CSSValueRtl)
1589 continue;
1590
1591 if (foundDirection != WritingDirection::Natural)
1592 return WritingDirection::Natural;
1593
1594 // In the range case, make sure that the embedding element persists until the end of the range.
1595 if (selection.isRange() && !end.deprecatedNode()->isDescendantOf(*node))
1596 return WritingDirection::Natural;
1597
1598 foundDirection = directionValue == CSSValueLtr ? WritingDirection::LeftToRight : WritingDirection::RightToLeft;
1599 }
1600 hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings = false;
1601 return foundDirection;
1602}
1603
1604Ref<EditingStyle> EditingStyle::inverseTransformColorIfNeeded(Element& element)
1605{
1606 auto* renderer = element.renderer();
1607 if (!m_mutableStyle || !renderer || !renderer->style().hasAppleColorFilter())
1608 return *this;
1609
1610 auto colorForPropertyIfInvertible = [&](CSSPropertyID id) -> std::optional<Color> {
1611 auto color = m_mutableStyle->propertyAsColor(id);
1612 if (!color || !color->isVisible() || color->isSemantic())
1613 return std::nullopt;
1614 return color;
1615 };
1616
1617 auto color = colorForPropertyIfInvertible(CSSPropertyColor);
1618 auto caretColor = colorForPropertyIfInvertible(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1619 auto backgroundColor = colorForPropertyIfInvertible(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1620 if (!color && !caretColor && !backgroundColor)
1621 return *this;
1622
1623 auto styleWithInvertedColors = copy();
1624 ASSERT(styleWithInvertedColors->m_mutableStyle);
1625
1626 const auto& colorFilter = renderer->style().appleColorFilter();
1627 auto invertedColor = [&](CSSPropertyID propertyID) {
1628 Color newColor = cssValueToColor(extractPropertyValue(*m_mutableStyle, propertyID).get());
1629 colorFilter.inverseTransformColor(newColor);
1630 styleWithInvertedColors->m_mutableStyle->setProperty(propertyID, serializationForCSS(newColor));
1631 };
1632
1633 if (color)
1634 invertedColor(CSSPropertyColor);
1635
1636 if (caretColor)
1637 invertedColor(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1638
1639 if (backgroundColor)
1640 invertedColor(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1641
1642 return styleWithInvertedColors;
1643}
1644
1645static void reconcileTextDecorationProperties(MutableStyleProperties* style)
1646{
1647 RefPtr<CSSValue> textDecorationsInEffect = style->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
1648 RefPtr<CSSValue> textDecoration = style->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
1649 // We shouldn't have both text-decoration and -webkit-text-decorations-in-effect because that wouldn't make sense.
1650 ASSERT(!textDecorationsInEffect || !textDecoration);
1651 if (textDecorationsInEffect) {
1652 style->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, textDecorationsInEffect->cssText());
1653 style->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
1654 textDecoration = textDecorationsInEffect;
1655 }
1656
1657 // If text-decoration is set to "none", remove the property because we don't want to add redundant "text-decoration: none".
1658 if (textDecoration && !textDecoration->isValueList())
1659 style->removeProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
1660}
1661
1662StyleChange::StyleChange(EditingStyle* style, const Position& position)
1663 : m_applyBold(false)
1664 , m_applyItalic(false)
1665 , m_applyUnderline(false)
1666 , m_applyLineThrough(false)
1667 , m_applySubscript(false)
1668 , m_applySuperscript(false)
1669{
1670 Document* document = position.deprecatedNode() ? &position.deprecatedNode()->document() : 0;
1671 if (!style || style->isEmpty() || !document || !document->frame())
1672 return;
1673
1674 Node* node = position.containerNode();
1675 if (!node)
1676 return;
1677
1678 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyle(node);
1679
1680 // FIXME: take care of background-color in effect
1681 RefPtr<MutableStyleProperties> mutableStyle = style->style() ?
1682 getPropertiesNotIn(*style->style(), computedStyle) : MutableStyleProperties::create();
1683
1684 reconcileTextDecorationProperties(mutableStyle.get());
1685 bool shouldStyleWithCSS = document->editor().shouldStyleWithCSS();
1686 if (!shouldStyleWithCSS)
1687 extractTextStyles(*document, *mutableStyle, computedStyle.useFixedFontDefaultSize());
1688
1689 bool shouldAddUnderline = style->underlineChange() == TextDecorationChange::Add;
1690 bool shouldAddStrikeThrough = style->strikeThroughChange() == TextDecorationChange::Add;
1691 if (shouldAddUnderline || shouldAddStrikeThrough) {
1692 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = computedStyle.propertyValue(CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
1693 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value))
1694 value = computedStyle.propertyValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
1695
1696 RefPtr<CSSValueList> valueList;
1697 if (is<CSSValueList>(value))
1698 valueList = downcast<CSSValueList>(value.get());
1699
1700 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1701 Ref<CSSValue> underline = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline);
1702 bool hasUnderline = valueList && valueList->hasValue(underline.ptr());
1703
1704 Ref<CSSValue> lineThrough = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough);
1705 bool hasLineThrough = valueList && valueList->hasValue(lineThrough.ptr());
1706
1707 if (shouldStyleWithCSS) {
1708 valueList = valueList ? valueList->copy() : CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1709 if (shouldAddUnderline && !hasUnderline)
1710 valueList->append(WTFMove(underline));
1711 if (shouldAddStrikeThrough && !hasLineThrough)
1712 valueList->append(WTFMove(lineThrough));
1713 mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyTextDecoration, valueList.get());
1714 } else {
1715 m_applyUnderline = shouldAddUnderline && !hasUnderline;
1716 m_applyLineThrough = shouldAddStrikeThrough && !hasLineThrough;
1717 }
1718 }
1719
1720 // Changing the whitespace style in a tab span would collapse the tab into a space.
1721 if (isTabSpanTextNode(position.deprecatedNode()) || isTabSpanNode((position.deprecatedNode())))
1722 mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyWhiteSpace);
1723
1724 // If unicode-bidi is present in mutableStyle and direction is not, then add direction to mutableStyle.
1725 // FIXME: Shouldn't this be done in getPropertiesNotIn?
1726 if (mutableStyle->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyUnicodeBidi) && !style->style()->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyDirection))
1727 mutableStyle->setProperty(CSSPropertyDirection, style->style()->getPropertyValue(CSSPropertyDirection));
1728
1729 if (!mutableStyle->isEmpty())
1730 m_cssStyle = mutableStyle;
1731}
1732
1733bool StyleChange::operator==(const StyleChange& other)
1734{
1735 if (m_applyBold != other.m_applyBold
1736 || m_applyItalic != other.m_applyItalic
1737 || m_applyUnderline != other.m_applyUnderline
1738 || m_applyLineThrough != other.m_applyLineThrough
1739 || m_applySubscript != other.m_applySubscript
1740 || m_applySuperscript != other.m_applySuperscript
1741 || m_applyFontColor != other.m_applyFontColor
1742 || m_applyFontFace != other.m_applyFontFace
1743 || m_applyFontSize != other.m_applyFontSize)
1744 return false;
1745
1746 return (!m_cssStyle && !other.m_cssStyle)
1747 || (m_cssStyle && other.m_cssStyle && m_cssStyle->asText() == other.m_cssStyle->asText());
1748}

1750static void setTextDecorationProperty(MutableStyleProperties& style, const CSSValueList* newTextDecoration, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
1751{
1752 if (newTextDecoration->length())
1753 style.setProperty(propertyID, newTextDecoration->cssText(), style.propertyIsImportant(propertyID));
1754 else {
1755 // text-decoration: none is redundant since it does not remove any text decorations.
1756 style.removeProperty(propertyID);
1757 }
1758}
1759
1760void StyleChange::extractTextStyles(Document& document, MutableStyleProperties& style, bool shouldUseFixedFontDefaultSize)
1761{
1762 if (identifierForStyleProperty(style, CSSPropertyFontWeight) == CSSValueBold) {
1763 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontWeight);
1764 m_applyBold = true;
1765 }
1766
1767 int fontStyle = identifierForStyleProperty(style, CSSPropertyFontStyle);
1768 if (fontStyle == CSSValueItalic || fontStyle == CSSValueOblique) {
1769 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontStyle);
1770 m_applyItalic = true;
1771 }
1772
1773 // Assuming reconcileTextDecorationProperties has been called, there should not be -webkit-text-decorations-in-effect
1774 // Furthermore, text-decoration: none has been trimmed so that text-decoration property is always a CSSValueList.
1775 RefPtr<CSSValue> textDecoration = style.getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
1776 if (is<CSSValueList>(textDecoration)) {
1777 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1778 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> underline = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline);
1779 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineThrough = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough);
1780
1781 RefPtr<CSSValueList> newTextDecoration = downcast<CSSValueList>(*textDecoration).copy();
1782 if (newTextDecoration->removeAll(underline.get()))
1783 m_applyUnderline = true;
1784 if (newTextDecoration->removeAll(lineThrough.get()))
1785 m_applyLineThrough = true;
1786
1787 // If trimTextDecorations, delete underline and line-through
1788 setTextDecorationProperty(style, newTextDecoration.get(), CSSPropertyTextDecoration);
1789 }
1790
1791 int verticalAlign = identifierForStyleProperty(style, CSSPropertyVerticalAlign);
1792 switch (verticalAlign) {
1793 case CSSValueSub:
1794 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyVerticalAlign);
1795 m_applySubscript = true;
1796 break;
1797 case CSSValueSuper:
1798 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyVerticalAlign);
1799 m_applySuperscript = true;
1800 break;
1801 }
1802
1803 if (style.getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyColor)) {
1804 auto color = textColorFromStyle(style);
1805 if (color.isOpaque()) {
1806 m_applyFontColor = serializationForHTML(color);
1807 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyColor);
1808 }
1809 }
1810
1811 m_applyFontFace = style.getPropertyValue(CSSPropertyFontFamily);
1812 // Remove quotes for Outlook 2007 compatibility. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79448
1813 m_applyFontFace.replaceWithLiteral('\"', "");
1814 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontFamily);
1815
1816 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> fontSize = style.getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyFontSize)) {
1817 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*fontSize))
1818 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontSize); // Can't make sense of the number. Put no font size.
1819 else if (int legacyFontSize = legacyFontSizeFromCSSValue(document, downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(fontSize.get()),
1820 shouldUseFixedFontDefaultSize, UseLegacyFontSizeOnlyIfPixelValuesMatch)) {
1821 m_applyFontSize = String::number(legacyFontSize);
1822 style.removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontSize);
1823 }
1824 }
1825}
1826
1827static void diffTextDecorations(MutableStyleProperties& style, CSSPropertyID propertID, CSSValue* refTextDecoration)
1828{
1829 RefPtr<CSSValue> textDecoration = style.getPropertyCSSValue(propertID);
1830 if (!is<CSSValueList>(textDecoration) || !is<CSSValueList>(refTextDecoration))
1831 return;
1832
1833 RefPtr<CSSValueList> newTextDecoration = downcast<CSSValueList>(*textDecoration).copy();
1834
1835 for (auto& value : downcast<CSSValueList>(*refTextDecoration))
1836 newTextDecoration->removeAll(&value.get());
1837
1838 setTextDecorationProperty(style, newTextDecoration.get(), propertID);
1839}
1840
1841static bool fontWeightIsBold(CSSValue& fontWeight)
1842{
1843 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(fontWeight))
1844 return false;
1845
1846 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(fontWeight);
1847 switch (primitiveValue.valueID()) {
1848 case CSSValueNormal:
1849 return false;
1850 case CSSValueBold:
1851 return true;
1852 default:
1853 break;
1854 }
1855
1856 ASSERT(primitiveValue.isNumber());
1857 return primitiveValue.floatValue() >= static_cast<float>(boldThreshold());
1858}
1859
1860template<typename T>
1861static bool fontWeightIsBold(T& style)
1862{
1863 RefPtr<CSSValue> fontWeight = extractPropertyValue(style, CSSPropertyFontWeight);
1864 return fontWeight && fontWeightIsBold(*fontWeight);
1865}
1866
1867template<typename T>
1868static Ref<MutableStyleProperties> extractPropertiesNotIn(StyleProperties& styleWithRedundantProperties, T& baseStyle)
1869{
1870 auto result = EditingStyle::create(&styleWithRedundantProperties);
1871 result->removeEquivalentProperties(baseStyle);
1872 ASSERT(result->style());
1873 Ref<MutableStyleProperties> mutableStyle = *result->style();
1874
1875 RefPtr<CSSValue> baseTextDecorationsInEffect = extractPropertyValue(baseStyle, CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect);
1876 diffTextDecorations(mutableStyle, CSSPropertyTextDecoration, baseTextDecorationsInEffect.get());
1877 diffTextDecorations(mutableStyle, CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecorationsInEffect, baseTextDecorationsInEffect.get());
1878
1879 if (extractPropertyValue(baseStyle, CSSPropertyFontWeight) && fontWeightIsBold(mutableStyle) == fontWeightIsBold(baseStyle))
1880 mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyFontWeight);
1881
1882 if (extractPropertyValue(baseStyle, CSSPropertyColor) && equalIgnoringSemanticColor(textColorFromStyle(mutableStyle), textColorFromStyle(baseStyle)))
1883 mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyColor);
1884
1885 if (extractPropertyValue(baseStyle, CSSPropertyCaretColor) && equalIgnoringSemanticColor(caretColorFromStyle(mutableStyle), caretColorFromStyle(baseStyle)))
1886 mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1887
1888 if (extractPropertyValue(baseStyle, CSSPropertyTextAlign)
1889 && textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(mutableStyle) == textAlignResolvingStartAndEnd(baseStyle))
1890 mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyTextAlign);
1891
1892 if (extractPropertyValue(baseStyle, CSSPropertyBackgroundColor) && equalIgnoringSemanticColor(backgroundColorFromStyle(mutableStyle), backgroundColorFromStyle(baseStyle)))
1893 mutableStyle->removeProperty(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1894
1895 return mutableStyle;
1896}

1900{
1901 return extractPropertiesNotIn(styleWithRedundantProperties, baseStyle);

1904static bool isCSSValueLength(CSSPrimitiveValue* value)
1905{
1906 return value->isFontIndependentLength();
1907}
1908
1909int legacyFontSizeFromCSSValue(Document& document, CSSPrimitiveValue* value, bool shouldUseFixedFontDefaultSize, LegacyFontSizeMode mode)
1910{
1911 if (isCSSValueLength(value)) {
1912 int pixelFontSize = value->intValue(CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
1913 int legacyFontSize = Style::legacyFontSizeForPixelSize(pixelFontSize, shouldUseFixedFontDefaultSize, document);
1914 // Use legacy font size only if pixel value matches exactly to that of legacy font size.
1915 int cssPrimitiveEquivalent = legacyFontSize - 1 + CSSValueXSmall;
1916 if (mode == AlwaysUseLegacyFontSize || Style::fontSizeForKeyword(cssPrimitiveEquivalent, shouldUseFixedFontDefaultSize, document) == pixelFontSize)
1917 return legacyFontSize;
1918
1919 return 0;
1920 }
1921
1922 if (CSSValueXSmall <= value->valueID() && value->valueID() <= CSSValueWebkitXxxLarge)
1923 return value->valueID() - CSSValueXSmall + 1;
1924
1925 return 0;
1926}
1927
1928static bool isTransparentColorValue(CSSValue* value)
1929{
1930 if (!value)
1931 return true;
1932 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value))
1933 return false;
1934 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value);
1935 if (primitiveValue.isRGBColor())
1936 return !primitiveValue.color().isVisible();
1937 return primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueTransparent;
1938}
1939
1940bool hasTransparentBackgroundColor(StyleProperties* style)
1941{
1942 return isTransparentColorValue(style->getPropertyCSSValue(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor).get());
1943}
1944
1945RefPtr<CSSValue> backgroundColorInEffect(Node* node)
1946{
1947 for (Node* ancestor = node; ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->parentNode()) {
1948 if (auto value = ComputedStyleExtractor(ancestor).propertyValue(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor)) {
1949 if (!isTransparentColorValue(value.get()))
1950 return value;
1951 }
1952 }
1953 return nullptr;
1954}
